100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 20, 1926, the world witnessed significant political shifts as the British Empire faced growing unrest in India, where calls for independence intensified. In Europe, the German government announced a new plan to stabilize its economy amidst ongoing hyperinflation, while in the United States, the Senate debated the ramifications of Prohibition, reflecting the nation's deepening divisions over the law. Meanwhile, advancements in aviation were celebrated with Charles Lindberghs recent transatlantic flight sparking public fascination and ambition in the field of air travel.
